<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="12" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="12.[120,650,788,1341]" pageId="12" pageNumber="12">
ETYMOLOGY: Taken directly from Cretaceous and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Woodley" baseAuthorityYear="2011" box="[168,225,1218,1242]" class="Insecta" family="Xylomyidae" genus="Solva" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[168,225,1218,1242]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="12">Solva</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but the name is not meant to imply a close relationship between it and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Woodley" baseAuthorityYear="2011" box="[483,540,1251,1275]" class="Insecta" family="Xylomyidae" genus="Solva" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[483,540,1251,1275]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="12">Solva</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The gen- der of the name is feminine.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
